      "message": "KVM: arm/arm64: vgic-new: Implement kvm_vgic_vcpu_pending_irq\n\nTell KVM whether a particular VCPU has an IRQ that needs handling\nin the guest. This is used to decide whether a VCPU is runnable.\n\nSigned-off-by: Eric Auger <f60a3d4b180725ab11fd137ffa53f5ae9a69db9a@linaro.org>\nSigned-off-by: Andre Przywara <94eb15b8f54b8e37c3f8d338296201be47dc5c3e@arm.com>\nReviewed-by: Christoffer Dall <39e5ecfe2ecc327c3e39af72d8d83d1bd0709aad@linaro.org>\nReviewed-by: Marc Zyngier <a16cc0c82647c52d401177f8e50567df5499e36c@arm.com>\n",
